{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "apex", "namespace": "apex", "internal": "rig::ExtractParmTransform", "icon": "APEX/rig-ExtractParmTransform-", "version": "", "tags": "apex", "since": "20.0"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["rig::ExtractParmTransform"], "extent": [155, 185]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Extracts the transformation parameters from a local matrix with respect to a local rest matrix."], "extent": [185, 289]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Extracts the translation, rotation, and scale parameters from a local space matrix with respect to a local space rest matrix. This node represents the inverse functionality of ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--CombineParmTransform-", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--CombineParmTransform-.html"}, ". The parameters are extracted such that they reverse the effects of the corresponding ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Pre-transform"]}, ", ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Post-transform"]}, ", or ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Override"]}, " transformation modes that could be used to recreate the local matrix. See the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/kinefx--rigpose", "type": "link", "text": ["Rig Pose SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/kinefx--rigpose.html"}, " for more details on these transform modes."], "extent": [289, 801]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node is useful in rig inversion workflows, where it can generate the parameter values needed to reproduce the pose described by the local matrix given an arbitrary rest matrix."], "extent": [801, 984]}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [984, 992], "body": [{"type": "inputs_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["local"], "role": "item", "extent": [992, 1003], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The local space matrix from which to extract the transformation parameters with respect to the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["inputlocal"]}, " matrix."], "extent": [1022, 1145]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Matrix4"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["inputlocal"], "role": "item", "extent": [1145, 1160], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The local space rest matrix."], "extent": [1179, 1213]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Matrix4"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["parentlocalscale"], "role": "item", "extent": [1213, 1234], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The scale values of the parent in the parent\u2019s local space. The scale values are extracted from the translation component of the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["inputlocal"]}, " matrix based on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["scaleinheritance"]}, " mode."], "extent": [1253, 1449]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Vector3"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["xord"], "role": "item", "extent": [1449, 1458], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The transformation order of the transformation parameters. The default is scale  \u2192 rotate  \u2192 translate. See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "TransformObject#transformation_construction", "type": "link", "text": ["transformation order"], "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/TransformObject.html#transformation_construction", "fragment": "#transformation_construction"}, "."], "extent": [1473, 1654]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["rord"], "role": "item", "extent": [1654, 1663], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The rotation order. The default is X  \u2192 Y  \u2192 Z. See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "TransformObject#transformation_construction", "type": "link", "text": ["rotation order"], "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/TransformObject.html#transformation_construction", "fragment": "#transformation_construction"}, "."], "extent": [1678, 1797]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["scaleinheritance"], "role": "item", "extent": [1797, 1818], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determines how the scale inheritance from the parent transform is extracted from the result."], "extent": [1833, 1931]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "inputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["method"], "role": "item", "extent": [1931, 1942], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The transformation mode, which affects how the transformation parameters are extracted from the rest matrix. The default is ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Pre-transform"]}, ". See the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/kinefx--rigpose", "type": "link", "text": ["Rig Pose SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/kinefx--rigpose.html"}, " for more details on the transform modes."], "extent": [1957, 2192]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Int"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2192, 2201], "body": [{"type": "outputs_item_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "outputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["t"], "role": "item", "extent": [2201, 2208], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The extracted translation."], "extent": [2227, 2259]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Vector3"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "outputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["r"], "role": "item", "extent": [2259, 2265], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The extracted rotation represented as Euler angles, in degrees. The rotation order corresponds to the value of ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["rord"]}, "."], "extent": [2284, 2410]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Vector3"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "outputs_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["s"], "role": "item", "extent": [2410, 2416], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The extracted scale."], "extent": [2435, 2461]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"type": "Vector3"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Outputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2461, 2470], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/rig--CombineParmTransform-", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/rig--CombineParmTransform-.html"}], "extent": [2470, 2511]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/apex/TransformObject", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/apex/TransformObject.html"}], "extent": [2511, 2541]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["rig::ExtractParmTransform"], "summary": ["Extracts the transformation parameters from a local matrix with respect to a local rest matrix."]}